comment.text: Transcriptional activator which binds to the enhancer of the T-cell receptor alpha and delta genes. Binds to the consensus sequence 5'-AGATAG-3'. Required for the T-helper 2 (Th2) differentiation process following immune and inflammatory responses.
Binds DNA via the 2 GATA-type zinc fingers. Each zinc finger may bind either adjacent sites in a palindromic motif, or a different DNA molecule allowing looping and long-range gene regulation.
The YxKxHxxxRP motif is critical for DNA-binding and function.

disease.name: Hypoparathyroidism, sensorineural deafness, and renal disease
disease.description: A disease characterized by steroid-resistant nephrosis with progressive renal failure, hypoparathyroidism, sensorineural deafness, and renal dysplasia.

comment.text: The disease is caused by mutations affecting the gene represented in this entry.
